latestPosts.caption:
MISS UNIVERSE INDIA 2025 NATIONAL FINALIST (WILD CARD) — LEKANA HEGDE ✨

Will she be the next Miss Universe India? @lekana_hegde 🇮🇳
______________________________________

Lekana Hegde is a 24-year-old professional model, national-level basketball player, and marketing postgraduate from Bengaluru, with roots in Mangalore. Standing 5’10.5” tall, she is currently pursuing her Master’s at Anglia Ruskin University, UK, on a basketball scholarship 🏀🎓

A 17-time Karnataka state player, she’s medalled at SGFI, Khelo India, and All India University Championships, while also walking for global fashion names at Dubai Fashion Week and top Indian designers like Tarun Tahiliani and Ritu Kumar 🏅👠

Lekana’s advocacy, Namma Kuteera, focuses on animal welfare and the rehabilitation of strays. Raised by a strong single mother, she believes in equity over equality — and in turning challenges into purpose-driven impact 🐾💫

MISS UNIVERSE INDIA 2025 NATIONAL FINALIST (WILD CARD) — SAUMYA VERMA ✨

Will she be the next Miss Universe India? @saumyasverma 🇮🇳
______________________________________

Saumya Verma is a 20-year-old psychology student and professional model from Delhi, standing tall at 5’9”. She has worked with top designers like Torani, Anju Modi, Biba, and Rana Gill, blending academic passion with fashion excellence 🎓👗

A creative spirit, Saumya is skilled in painting, singing, dancing, and styling — often the fashion guide among her friends. She’s also interned with a clinical psychologist, deepening her understanding of mental health, which she actively advocates for 🎨🧠

Grounded in gratitude and driven by purpose, she supports underprivileged children and hopes to inspire others through kindness, creativity, and staying true to oneself 💛🌟

MISS UNIVERSE INDIA 2025 NATIONAL FINALIST (WILD CARD) — SAANVI SHARMA ✨

Will she be the next Miss Universe India? @saanviisharma 🇮🇳
______________________________________

Saanvi Sharma is a 23-year-old educator and postgraduate student from Himachal Pradesh, currently based in Ghaziabad. Standing 5’4” tall and fluent in Hindi, English, and Dogri, she mentors young learners through her role at an edtech firm 📚✨

A Philosophy graduate with a deep love for life, learning, and the arts, Saanvi connects through dance, singing, and writing. Once someone who dimmed her light to fit in, she now rises with purpose and confidence 🌱🩰

Her advocacy champions mental health and women’s empowerment — shaped by her own journey of resilience. For Saanvi, every comeback is a chance to shine brighter and uplift others through grace and grit 💫🤍

MISS UNIVERSE INDIA 2025 NATIONAL FINALIST (WILD CARD) — MANIKA VISHWAKARMA ✨

Will she be the next Miss Universe India? @mani_navrang 🇮🇳
______________________________________

Manika Vishwakarma is a 5’7” tall model and nationally awarded artist from Sri Ganganagar, Rajasthan, currently based in Delhi. A final-year student of Political Science and Economics, she recently won the Miss Universe Rajasthan 2024 title 🏛️🎨

From classical dance and painting to representing India at BIMSTEC Sewocon under the Ministry of External Affairs, Manika’s journey bridges intellect and creativity. Honoured by Lalit Kala Academy and JJ School of Arts, she is also a celebrated public speaker and performer 🩰🎙️

Founder of Neuronova, her advocacy reframes neurodivergence — especially ADHD — as a unique way of thinking, not a disorder. Through her initiative, she champions authenticity, empathy, and embracing cognitive diversity 🧠💡

MISS UNIVERSE INDIA 2025 NATIONAL FINALIST (WILD CARD) — RAKSHA JAISWAL ✨

Will she be the next Miss Universe India? 
@rakshaj_08 🇮🇳
______________________________________

Raksha Jaiswal is a 22-year-old model and actor born in Prayagraj and based in Mumbai. She moved to the city at 10 and soon discovered her calling in dance and acting — expressive forms that helped her stay connected to her mind and body 🎭💃

Currently pursuing a degree in Science and Technology, Raksha is fluent in English, Hindi, and Marathi, and also skilled in singing and dancing. She chose passion over pressure, embracing the arts despite early expectations of a medical career 🎓🎶

Her advocacy focuses on raising awareness about learning disabilities, working to break stigma and create supportive spaces that celebrate different ways of learning and growing 🧠💙

MISS UNIVERSE INDIA 2025 NATIONAL FINALIST (WILD CARD) — RIDDHI KUMAR ✨

Will she be the next Miss Universe India? @riddhikumar_ 🇮🇳
______________________________________

Riddhi Kumar is a 27-year-old Actor born in Kopargaon, Maharashtra, raised across India as the daughter of an Indian Army officer. Standing 5’6” tall, this multilingual performer knows 7 languages and blends discipline, adaptability, and artistic depth. She is also currently pursuing her Master’s in Philosophy, having completed her Bachelor’s from Fergusson College, Pune. 🎭 📖 

A trained Kathak dancer and has won many pageants since her teens, Riddhi has acted in Telugu, Malayalam, and Hindi films and web series — including Crash Course, Human, Superboys of Malegaon, and an upcoming film opposite Prabhas titled The Raja Saab. 🎬🪷✨ 

Her advocacy for women’s empowerment includes launching a social enterprise for financial literacy and creative skill development among underprivileged women, while actively leading environmental clean-up drives and sustainability projects. ♻️💪🏻

MISS UNIVERSE INDIA 2025 NATIONAL FINALIST (WILD CARD) — ASMITA CHOWDHURY ✨

Will she be the next Miss Universe India? @_asmitachowdhury 🇮🇳
______________________________________

Asmita Chowdhury is a 24-year-old model from Ahmedabad with a background in Computer Science and ISRO training. Now pursuing her Master’s in Fashion Management at NIFT, she’s blending intellect with creativity and standing tall at 5’2” with purpose-driven ambition 🎓✨

A singer, actor, and polyglot fluent in five languages, Asmita won five crowns in 2021 — not for validation, but to spark transformation. Her initiative UDAAN champions value-based education and empowers those who’ve been underestimated to rise 📖🔥

Rooted in resilience and driven by purpose, she continues to redefine what it means to lead with both heart and intellect 💫🤝

MISS UNIVERSE INDIA 2025 NATIONAL FINALIST (WILD CARD) — SANJANA SOOD ✨

Will she be the next Miss Universe India? @saanjjana 🇮🇳
______________________________________

Sanjana Sood is an actor, singer, and performer from Faridabad, born in Delhi, with roots tracing back to Kenya and Rawalpindi. A graduate in Economics and Mathematics and a trained actor from the National School of Drama, she’s also a former international-level shooter 🎭📚

Bullied for acne during school, Sanjana discovered her strength and voice through the performing arts during lockdown. She released her first song and is now building a culturally rooted Indian girl group to bridge Indian and global pop music 🌍🎶

A freestyle dancer, songwriter, singer, and sustainability advocate, Sanjana’s journey is driven by creativity, resilience, and a mission to make Indian artistry globally recognized and environmentally conscious 💃♻️

MISS UNIVERSE INDIA 2025 NATIONAL FINALIST (WILD CARD) — ROOSH SINDHU ✨

Will she be the next Miss Universe India? @rooshsindhu 🇮🇳
______________________________________

Roosh Sindhu is a 5’7” tall author, mental health activist, professional model, and TEDx speaker from Nagpur, now based in New Delhi. A Journalism graduate with a Fashion Design certification from INIFD, she also represented India as a certified student designer at New York Fashion Week 2019 🧠📚

The author of Universe Within Peace, Roosh has over six years of Psychology training and runs an NGO — Moralize Mental Health Association — through which she conducts free anxiety assessments, support groups, and awareness sessions across India 💬🧠

From being bullied as a child to becoming an NCC sergeant, international marketing professional, and award-winning social contributor, Roosh now advocates emotional healing, mental health education, and dreams of inspiring through cinema and motivational speaking 🎤🎬
